<!--Jumbotron-->
<div class="section fade-in">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row g-4 philosophy-grid mx-auto">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="philosophy-card">
          <h1 style="font-family: 'Gill Sans', 'Gill Sans MT', Calibri, 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"class="title">I Believe That All People are Musical</h1>
          <p class="philosophy-text">
            We all show up with different skills and deficits. Let's fill in the deficits and nurture the skills together.
            While each of my student's piano education is individualized, I do have a multifaceted approach encompassing three main concepts:
          </p>
          <p class="philosophy-text" style="font-style: italic;">1. The aural experience: What kind of sound am I making with my instrument?</p>
          <p class="philosophy-text" style="font-style: italic;">2. The physical experience: Do I have freedom, comfort, and ease while playing my instrument?</p>
          <p class="philosophy-text" style="font-style: italic;">3. The spatial experience: In our instance, as it relates to the reading of music and the geography of the keyboard.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="philosophy-card">
          <h1 style="font-family: 'Gill Sans', 'Gill Sans MT', Calibri, 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"class="title">My Approach</h1>
          <p style="font-size: larger;" class="philosophy-text">
            My approach is contingent first and foremost upon nurturing a curiosity, love, and enjoyment of playing the piano.
            Learning to play the piano is both an adventure and a journey — let's experience the process together!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
